  "abstract": "Pigeonpea (Cajanus cajan (L.) Millsp.) is one of the most important grain\r\nlegume components of subsistence farming systems in the semi-arid\r\ntropics. Many fungi, viruses, nematodes, bacteria, and mycoplasmalike\r\norganisms attack pigeonpea, but only a few of these are important\r\nconstraints to pigeonpea production. This bulletin provides information\r\non the causal agents, distribution, economic importance, symptoms,\r\nepidemiology, and management of major diseases of pigeonpea. The\r\ntext is supplemented with color photographs of disease symptoms and a\r\ndiagnostic key is included to facilitate identification. Information provided\r\non control measures includes the use of resistant varieties, cultural\r\npractices and chemicals. Supporting literature on the major diseases\r\nis listed.",
